bug.short_desc: Homepage: The button links ( Introduction, Demo, ...) are displayed in two overlapping rows which looks ugly

long_desc.thetext: Using the default Firefox 3.06 under Ubuntu 8.10 (Intrepid Ibex) has the button link "License" be partly on top of the link "Introduction". On Windows (IE and FIrefox) this is ok. After some searching this is because the active CSS for those buttons (div.notehighlight) has a font definition: font-family: "Trebuchet MS", "Lucida Grande", Verdana, sans-serif; resulting into sans-serif, which default under ubunut is wider than the other fonts specified and pushes the stuff out to a second line. Changing the default font for sans serif in Firefox to "Nimbus Sans L" makes things look much better, so I assume adding that to the font-family list would improve things for visitors to your site. As it is the first page I got to I think this is important (hence the severity). As I don't see a button to attach some file to this report here is a link to a screenshot of how it looks: http://www.xs4all.nl/~anthon/qooxdoo-ubuntu8.10-firefox.png
Created attachment 449 Screenshot of the first page please note the ugly overlap of 'License'

Hi Anthon, changed font resolution by introducing "Nimbus Sans L". Could you please confirm that this resolves the issue? I close this bug now, but if the issue should unexpectedly still exist, please reopen it.
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
